brainrotfilter (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * APPLIANCE RELEASE — preparing for physical transparent-bridge deployment.
  * ICAP body-inspection service (brainrotfilter-icap.service) — reads
    YouTube /youtubei/v1/(player|next) POST bodies to extract videoId
    even when watch URLs are cached. Log-only by default.
  * Supervisor watchdog (brainrotfilter-watchdog.service) — per-service
    health + auto-restart with per-hour rate limit, plus /status admin page.
  * Pre-emptive CDN deny with per-client/per-video tracking, 40s TTL,
    auto-release on navigation to allowed content.
  * Squid configuration parity with field-validated live config: ICAP
    directives, host_verify_strict off, shim ACL whitelist, rewriter
    concurrency=1, extended playback-URL regex.
  * Transparent-bridge wizard (configure_bridge): 2-NIC → br0 netplan,
    br_netfilter sysctls, no NAT MASQUERADE. Interface picker with MAC
    / link state / speed.
  * BTRFS + snapper integration: factory snapshot taken post-wizard
    on BTRFS root, rollback via TUI or /api/system/rollback.
  * Config backup & restore: /backup admin page, export DB + env +
    keyword JSONs + Squid fragments as a gzipped tar, import with
    version compatibility check + .bak safety copies + service restart.
  * Console TUI on tty1 (pfSense-style): system status, interface
    re-assignment, management IP, factory reset, service restart,
    update, SSH toggle (disabled by default), shell, reboot/shutdown.
  * Persistent CA certificate admin page at /ca-cert with per-OS
    install instructions (Windows, macOS, iOS, Android, Chromebook,
    Linux).
  * Packaging: ships squid_cdn_block_helper.sh, icap + watchdog +
    console systemd units, all new Python modules. Depends now
    include iptables-persistent, bridge-utils, ebtables. Recommends
    btrfs-progs, snapper, dialog, python3-httpx.
  * Postinst creates /var/lib/brainrotfilter writable for watchdog,
    enables icap + watchdog services, disables SSH by default.
  * Custom Ubuntu ISO build pipeline (iso/) — live-build config for
    a stripped hardened appliance image with BrainrotFilter preinstalled.
  * DEPLOYMENT.md — full physical deployment guide: hardware (NIC
    recommendations, mini-PC suggestions), topology diagram, CA
    distribution, hardening manifest, TUI reference, troubleshooting.

