brainrotfilter (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Block enforcement: per-client CDN deny holds while a blocked video's
    URLs are still being requested (90s TTL refreshed by stats URLs);
    plus URL-level ACL denial of watch/stats URLs for blocked videos.
  * Defensive CDN fallback (Option B): client_ip without a recent
    /api/check identification gets googlevideo.com denied. Heartbeat
    keeps active sessions warm even when telemetry URLs lack docid.
  * Squid pre-filter: url_regex gates external helpers so home-page
    scrolling no longer floods them; helper pools bumped to 20 children
    with 3-5 startup; CDN helper keyed on %SRC only with 3s TTL.
  * Strong/weak signal split: only navigation URLs (watch/shorts/embed/
    youtu.be) queue analysis. Storyboards and stats URLs identify the
    client but never queue, so feed scrolling can't fill Processing.
  * Pre-emptive CDN blocking via brainrot_cdn_pending external_acl_type
    and squid_cdn_block_helper.sh.
  * iptables block via state_killer reduced to 30s (was 7200s); used
    only for the immediate RST window. Sustained blocking is handled by
    the per-client CDN deny instead.
  * /api/check endpoint records identify for any client_ip even without
    a video_id (covers heartbeats and channel-only checks).
  * Added /api/client-pending endpoint used by the CDN helper.
  * Block/warning page templates now receive flat variables (video_title,
    combined_score, scores, matched_keywords) instead of a nested dict
    that the template couldn't unpack.
  * Videos API: added 'limit' alias for per_page; raised cap to 2000;
    default sort now analyzed_at DESC.
  * app.js: relativeTime/formatDate append 'Z' to naive UTC timestamps
    so the dashboard shows correct local times.
  * Removed global googlevideo.com delay_pool — allowed videos now play
    at full native quality; throttling no longer needed because pre-
    emptive CDN deny handles unanalyzed-video pre-buffering.

